The next section explains "technology level" and its effect on
product quality.

pos : 249, 103
openmenu : 3, 5
To find out more about technology, look at the technology section
of the corporate detail report.

runmenu : 3, 5

pos : 452, 58, 530, 66
mouse : left single
Select "Technology".

The technology report shows information about your corporation's
R&D plans. The "Top Tech." column, displays the highest level of
technology ever used in production of the product.

pos :  298, 166
In the beginning of the game, the top technology level of all
products is 100. When a product with a higher technology level
hits the market, the top technology level is updated accordingly.

The top technology level is closely related to product quality.
Launching a product with an unprecedented technology level into
the market can cause the existing products to become inferior.

For example, if your technology level for beer production is 50,
and the top technology is 100, your product gains 27 quality
points in production. (55% of beer quality is determined by
production, so 55 X 50 / 100 = 27.) If the top technology were
200, the result would be much different. Your product could gain
only 50 X 50 / 200 = 13 quality points in the product part.

Thus, a high production technology level does not guarantee a
high quality rating, unless the technology level of your factory
is close to the top technology level.

pos : 212, 433, 231, 446
mouse : left single
Now you should have no problem understanding the technology
report, click here to close it.

When a research is complete, you can apply the results, that is
the improved production technology, to your manufacturing units.
You find the "Upgrade Tech" button in your manufacturing
units that are eligible for a technology upgrade. Press the
button to upgrade the production facilities of the unit to the new
technology and enable manufacture of better-quality products.
However, the unit's productivity may drop as the workers adapt to
the new production facilities.

R&D is critical to the success of a manufacturing business, but
you have to figure out yourself how to go about it. Now you are
ready to move on to the next lesson.
